style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin:0pt;"><a name="_Hlk152854357"></a><a name="_Hlk152854371"></a><b style="font-weight:bold;">King of Prussia, PA &#8212; (December 13, 2023) </b><b style="font-weight:bold;">&#8212;</b>Vertex, Inc. (NASDAQ: VERX), a global provider of indirect tax solutions, today announced that it has commenced a public tender offer for 100% of the shares of Pagero Group AB (publ) (&#8220;Pagero&#8221;) at a price of 36 SEK in cash per share, equivalent to a total tender value of approximately $555 million<sup style="font-size:8.25pt;vertical-align:top;"><a style="vertical-align:super;" href="#footnote-3">1</a></sup>. </p><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin:0pt;"><font style="line-height:1.28;margin-bottom:8pt;visibility:hidden;">&#8203;</font></p><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin:0pt;">Vertex&#8217;s acquisition of Pagero will accelerate the companies&#8217; partnership announced in October 2023 to provide multinational companies with an end-to-end solution to automate business transactions and manage indirect tax, reporting and e-invoicing compliance globally. E-invoicing has quickly become a necessity for businesses transacting in multiple jurisdictions with the rise of real-time and near-real time digital tax reporting government mandates. Pagero provides comprehensive solutions to automate e-invoicing compliance through its Smart Business Network. </p><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin:0pt;"><font style="line-height:1.28;margin-bottom:8pt;visibility:hidden;">&#8203;</font></p><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin:0pt;">Leveraging Pagero&#8217;s platform and global network, Vertex will extend its leadership by adding new digital transformation and e-invoicing capabilities to its portfolio to support customers in the rapidly changing, regulatory compliance landscape. The combined platform will help customers seamlessly <font style="color:#333333;">facilitate the creation, exchange, and clearance of jurisdictionally-compliant e-invoices, </font>enabling companies to reduce friction and other barriers to geographic expansion, and improve efficiency of their compliance and reporting operations. </p><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin:0pt;"><font style="line-height:1.28;margin-bottom:8pt;visibility:hidden;">&#8203;</font></p><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin:0pt;">&#8220;Vertex and Pagero have a shared vision to accelerate global commerce and help companies automate and digitize their compliance operations,&#8221; noted Vertex CEO David DeStefano. &#8220;Since the launch of our commercial partnership, we have seen strong reception from customers and partners. E-invoicing has become one of the fastest growing challenges facing our global enterprise customers, making this transaction a logical next step. We are confident that together, we will create a best-in-class solution for all indirect tax and e-invoicing needs to help customers navigate complex and evolving compliance mandates, expand our international reach, and unlock additional value for shareholders.&#8221; </p><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin:0pt;"><font style="font-family:'Times New Roman','Times','serif';font-size:12pt;line-height:1.28;margin-bottom:8pt;visibility:hidden;">&#8203;</font></p><div style="margin-bottom:5pt;margin-top:15pt;width:25%;border-bottom:1px solid black;"></div><a name="footnote-3"></a><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:10pt;line-height:1.19;margin:0pt;"><a name="_Hlk152854381"></a><sup style="font-size:7.5pt;vertical-align:top;">1</sup> Based upon ~161 million currently outstanding shares of Pagero and a USD / SEK exchange rate of 10.46. </p></div></div><hr style="background-color:#000000;clear:both;color:#000000;height:2pt;line-height:0;margin-bottom:30pt;margin-left:11.76%;margin-right:11.76%;margin-top:30pt;page-break-after:always;width:76.47%;border-width:0;"><div style="max-width:100%;padding-left:11.76%;padding-right:11.76%;position:relative;"><div style="margin-top:30pt;min-height:36pt;width:100%;"><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;text-align:right;margin:0pt;"><font style="display:inline-block;width:200.59pt;"></font>Exhibit 99.1</p></div><div style="clear:both;max-width:100%;position:relative;"><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin:0pt;">&#8220;Vertex has been a great partner in Pagero&#8217;s work to address pressing customer needs for best-in-class tax compliance solutions,&#8221; said Bengt Nilsson, Pagero&#8217;s second largest shareholder and CEO. &#8220;With the rapid emergence of new and proposed e-invoicing mandates and the digitization of indirect tax, e-invoicing has quickly become a necessity for businesses trading in multiple global jurisdictions. By combining Vertex and Pagero&#8217;s leading technologies, I am convinced we can better support customers while delivering meaningful value for shareholders.&#8221;</p><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin:0pt;"><font style="line-height:1.28;margin-bottom:8pt;visibility:hidden;">&#8203;</font></p><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin:0pt;"><b style="font-weight:bold;">Strategic and Financial Benefits of the Proposed Acquisition</b></p><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin:0pt;"><font style="line-height:1.28;margin-bottom:8pt;visibility:hidden;">&#8203;</font></p><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin:0pt;">Vertex believes acquiring Pagero will provide significant benefits to stakeholders of the combined company, including: </p><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin:0pt;"><font style="line-height:1.28;margin-bottom:8pt;visibility:hidden;">&#8203;</font></p><table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="border-collapse:collapse;font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;table-layout:fixed;width:100%;border:0pt;"><tr><td style="width:18pt;"></td><td style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;vertical-align:text-top;white-space:nowrap;width:18pt;padding:0pt;">-</td><td style="padding:0pt;"><b style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;font-style:normal;font-weight:bold;">Significantly Expands Market Opportunity:</b><font style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;"> The e-invoicing market is large and growing, driven by legislation and an increasingly complex compliance environment for companies to navigate. By extending its leadership into e-invoicing through Pagero, Vertex expects to expand its market opportunity from $22 billion to nearly $28 billion</font><sup style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:8.25pt;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;vertical-align:top;"><a style="vertical-align:super;" href="#footnote-4">2</a></sup><font style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;"> with considerable upside opportunities as the company helps customers navigate evolving compliance mandates globally. </font></td></tr></table><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt;"><font style="line-height:1.28;margin-bottom:8pt;margin-left:0pt;visibility:hidden;">&#8203;</font></p><table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="border-collapse:collapse;font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;table-layout:fixed;width:100%;border:0pt;"><tr><td style="width:18pt;"></td><td style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;vertical-align:text-top;white-space:nowrap;width:18pt;padding:0pt;">-</td><td style="padding:0pt;"><b style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;font-style:normal;font-weight:bold;">Advances International Growth Strategy:</b><font style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;"> Today, Pagero supports a network of approximately 14 million companies across 140 countries. The business&#8217; opportunity is rapidly expanding as more than 50 countries have currently adopted or are expected to adopt Continuous Transaction Controls (&#8220;CTC&#8221;) mandates. To address these requirements, customers are seeking solutions that simplify </font><font style="color:#333333;font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;">their returns and reporting</font><font style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;"> processes. Vertex expects to capitalize on this demand by leveraging Pagero&#8217;s e-invoicing solutions for existing customers and as an entry point for new customer acquisition.</font></td></tr></table><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin:0pt;"><font style="line-height:1.28;margin-bottom:8pt;visibility:hidden;">&#8203;</font></p><table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="border-collapse:collapse;font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;table-layout:fixed;width:100%;border:0pt;"><tr><td style="width:18pt;"></td><td style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;vertical-align:text-top;white-space:nowrap;width:18pt;padding:0pt;">-</td><td style="padding:0pt;"><b style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;font-style:normal;font-weight:bold;">In-Demand, Strategically Aligned Solutions to Manage Tax Compliance in the Digital Era: </b><font style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;">CTC and e-invoicing are key components in streamlining compliance processes and ensuring timely and accurate reporting. Through this transaction, Vertex will create a seamless, end-to-end compliance platform combining indirect tax, periodic filing and reporting and e-invoicing, with a scalable, open business network that will enable continuous compliance and operational efficiencies across the procure-to-pay and order-to-cash processes. </font></td></tr></table><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt;"><font style="line-height:1.28;margin-bottom:8pt;margin-left:0pt;visibility:hidden;">&#8203;</font></p><table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="border-collapse:collapse;font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;table-layout:fixed;width:100%;border:0pt;"><tr><td style="width:18pt;"></td><td style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;vertical-align:text-top;white-space:nowrap;width:18pt;padding:0pt;">-</td><td style="padding:0pt;"><b style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;font-style:normal;font-weight:bold;">Meaningful Growth Opportunities:</b><font style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;"> Pagero </font><font style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;">delivered year over year growth of 35% in its most recent fiscal quarter, and enjoys </font><font style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;">strong customer retention metrics. The transaction is expected to unlock additional value as the combined company supports customers at more points through their compliance processes globally. Vertex expects that deepening and expanding customer relationships will drive increased revenue growth. </font></td></tr></table><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt;"><font style="line-height:1.28;margin-bottom:8pt;margin-left:0pt;visibility:hidden;">&#8203;</font></p><table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="border-collapse:collapse;font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;table-layout:fixed;width:100%;border:0pt;"><tr><td style="width:18pt;"></td><td style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;vertical-align:text-top;white-space:nowrap;width:18pt;padding:0pt;">-</td><td style="padding:0pt;"><b style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;font-style:normal;font-weight:bold;">Enhanced Financial Profile:</b><font style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;"> Vertex expects the acquisition of Pagero to accelerate the Company&#8217;s pro-forma top-line growth by nearly 200 basis points, with a</font><font style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;"> near-term path to profit margin expansion</font><font style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;">. Pagero is expected to be accretive to Vertex&#8217;s margins in the second full year after closing, with additional opportunity to increase revenue synergies and cost benefits in the medium to long term. </font></td></tr></table><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin:0pt;"><font style="line-height:1.28;margin-bottom:8pt;visibility:hidden;">&#8203;</font></p><div style="margin-bottom:5pt;margin-top:15pt;width:25%;border-bottom:1px solid black;"></div><a name="footnote-4"></a><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:10pt;line-height:1.19;margin:0pt;"><sup style="font-size:7.5pt;vertical-align:top;">2</sup> Based on Vertex estimates</p></div></div><hr style="background-color:#000000;clear:both;color:#000000;height:2pt;line-height:0;margin-bottom:30pt;margin-left:11.76%;margin-right:11.76%;margin-top:30pt;page-break-after:always;width:76.47%;border-width:0;"><div style="max-width:100%;padding-left:11.76%;padding-right:11.76%;position:relative;"><div style="margin-top:30pt;min-height:36pt;width:100%;"><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;text-align:right;margin:0pt;"><font style="display:inline-block;width:200.59pt;"></font>Exhibit 99.1</p></div><div style="clear:both;max-width:100%;position:relative;"><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin:0pt;">Vertex has been informed by the independent bid committee of the Board of Directors of Pagero of its resolution to unanimously recommend the shareholders of Pagero to accept the public offer made by Vertex. Vertex has also received irrevocable undertakings to accept the Offer from Pagero&#8217;s two largest shareholders &#8211; V&#229;l&#229;uggen Invest AB which is controlled by Summa Equity and Greenfield AB and Norelia AB which are both controlled by Pagero&#8217;s CEO Bengt Nilsson &#8211; in total representing approximately 40.4 per cent of the outstanding shares in Pagero.</p><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin:0pt;"><font style="line-height:1.28;margin-bottom:8pt;visibility:hidden;">&#8203;</font></p><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin:0pt;"><b style="font-weight:bold;">Transaction Details</b></p><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin:0pt;"><a name="_Hlk152854391"></a><a name="_Hlk152854411"></a>The acceptance period of the offer is expected to commence on or around December 15, 2023 and expire on or around January 23, 2024. An offer document is expected to be made public on or around December 14, 2023. Assuming that the offer is declared unconditional after the acceptance period, settlement is expected to begin on or around February 1, 2024.</p><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin:0pt;"><font style="line-height:1.28;margin-bottom:8pt;visibility:hidden;">&#8203;</font></p><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin:0pt;"><a name="_Hlk152854396"></a>The offer is subject to certain regulatory approvals, the receipt of valid tenders of more than 90% of Pagero&#8217;s shares and customary closing conditions. </p><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin:0pt;"><font style="line-height:1.28;margin-bottom:8pt;visibility:hidden;">&#8203;</font></p><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin:0pt;"><a name="_Hlk152854400"></a>The per-share consideration noted above represents an approximate 71.4 percent premium to Pagero&#8217;s closing price on December 12, 2023, and a 77.1 percent premium to its prior 30-day volume-weighted average price on the same day and a 97.9 percent premium compared to the volume-weighted average price during the last 90 trading days ended on December 12, 2023.</p><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin:0pt;"><font style="line-height:1.28;margin-bottom:8pt;visibility:hidden;">&#8203;</font></p><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin:0pt;">This press release shall not constitute an offer to buy or a solicitation of an offer to sell any Pagero securities. The offer will be made solely pursuant to the applicable offer document, when available. The offer is not being made to holders of securities in any jurisdiction in which the making or acceptance thereof would not be in compliance with the securities, blue sky or other laws of such jurisdiction. The full details of the offer, including complete instructions on how to tender Pagero shares, will be included in the offer document.</p><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin:0pt;"><font style="line-height:1.28;margin-bottom:8pt;visibility:hidden;">&#8203;</font></p><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin:0pt;"><b style="font-weight:bold;">Financing Details</b></p><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin:0pt;">Vertex intends to fund the transaction with proceeds from its existing undrawn revolving credit facility and from issuance of a new series of Convertible Preferred Stock in the amount of $500 million to Silver Lake, the global leader in technology investing. Vertex welcomes Silver Lake not only as an investor but also as a strategic partner as Vertex expands its growth ambitions across technologies and geographies.</p><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin:0pt;"><font style="line-height:1.28;margin-bottom:8pt;visibility:hidden;">&#8203;</font></p><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin:0pt;">Joe Osnoss, a Managing Partner of Silver Lake, will join the Vertex Board of Directors upon transaction close. </p><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin:0pt;"><font style="line-height:1.28;margin-bottom:8pt;visibility:hidden;">&#8203;</font></p><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin:0pt;"><a name="_Hlk152854474"></a>Osnoss said, &#8220;Silver Lake has long regarded Vertex as an important pioneer, innovator and leader in enterprise technology solutions for global indirect tax compliance. Adding e-invoicing via Pagero will provide even more value to customers seeking end-to-end integration and automation. We are grateful for the opportunity to work with CEO David DeStefano and Vertex&#8217;s management in developing a long-term partnership between our firms.&#8221;</p><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin:0pt;"><font style="line-height:1.28;margin-bottom:8pt;visibility:hidden;">&#8203;</font></p><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin:0pt;"><a name="_Hlk152854480"></a>The issuance of the Convertible Preferred Stock is conditioned upon closing the acquisition. It carries a payment-in-kind dividend of 11.75% and is convertible into Vertex common stock at an initial conversion price equal to a 20% premium over Vertex&#8217;s trailing 10-day volume-weighted average price as of December 19, 2023, subject to a minimum conversion price of $32.50 and a maximum of $37.50. The Convertible Preferred Stock is redeemable on the terms and subject to the conditions set forth in the </p></div></div><hr style="background-color:#000000;clear:both;color:#000000;height:2pt;line-height:0;margin-bottom:30pt;margin-left:11.76%;margin-right:11.76%;margin-top:30pt;page-break-after:always;width:76.47%;border-width:0;"><div style="max-width:100%;padding-left:11.76%;padding-right:11.76%;position:relative;"><div style="margin-top:30pt;min-height:36pt;width:100%;"><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;text-align:right;margin:0pt;"><font style="display:inline-block;width:200.59pt;"></font>Exhibit 99.1</p></div><div style="clear:both;max-width:100%;position:relative;"><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin:0pt;">definitive agreements. As part of the transaction, Silver Lake will also be issued warrants to purchase up to 2.5 million additional shares of Vertex common stock at the conversion price. Vertex intends to file a Current Report with the Securities and Exchange Commission on Form 8-K that will have further details concerning the acquisition and the related financings.</p><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin:0pt;"><font style="line-height:1.28;margin-bottom:8pt;visibility:hidden;">&#8203;</font></p><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin:0pt;"><b style="font-weight:bold;">Conference call</b></p><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin:0pt;"><a name="_Hlk152854498"></a>Vertex will host a conference call at 8:30 AM ET / 2:30 PM CET today, December 13, 2023, to discuss the Pagero tender offer. </p><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin:0pt;"><font style="line-height:1.28;margin-bottom:8pt;visibility:hidden;">&#8203;</font></p><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin:0pt;">Those wishing to participate may do so by dialing 1-877-407-4018 or 1-201-689-8471 approximately ten minutes prior to start time. A listen-only webcast of the call will also be available through the Company&#8217;s Investor Relations website at https://ir.Vertexinc.com.</p><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin:0pt;"><font style="line-height:1.28;margin-bottom:8pt;visibility:hidden;">&#8203;</font></p><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin:0pt;">A conference call replay will be available approximately one hour after the call by dialing 1-844-512-2921 or 1-412-317-6671 and referencing passcode 13743202, or via the Company&#8217;s Investor Relations website. The replay will expire on December 27, 2023 at 11:59 p.m. Eastern Time.</p><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin:0pt;"><font style="font-weight:bold;line-height:1.28;margin-bottom:8pt;visibility:hidden;">&#8203;</font></p><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin:0pt;"><b style="font-weight:bold;">Advisors</b></p><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin:0pt;">Greenhill acted as financial advisor and DLA Piper acted as legal advisor to Vertex. Centerview Partners LLC acted as financial advisor and Latham and Watkins LLP as legal advisor to Vertex in connection with the investment by Silver Lake. </p><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin:0pt;"><font style="line-height:1.28;margin-bottom:8pt;visibility:hidden;">&#8203;</font></p><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin:0pt;"><a name="_Hlk153184669"></a><a name="_Hlk152854509"></a>Simpson Thacher &amp; Bartlett LLP acted as legal advisor to Silver Lake.</p><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin:0pt;"><font style="line-height:1.28;margin-bottom:8pt;visibility:hidden;">&#8203;</font></p><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin:0pt;"><b style="font-weight:bold;">About Vertex</b></p><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin:0pt;">Vertex, Inc. is a leading global provider of indirect tax solutions. The Company&#8217;s mission is to deliver the most trusted tax technology enabling global businesses to transact, comply and grow with confidence. Vertex provides solutions that can be tailored to specific industries for major lines of indirect tax, including sales and consumer use, value added and payroll. Headquartered in North America, and with offices in South America and Europe, Vertex employs over 1,400 professionals and serves companies across the globe.</p><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin:0pt;"><font style="line-height:1.28;margin-bottom:8pt;visibility:hidden;">&#8203;</font></p><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin:0pt;">For more information, visit www.Vertexinc.com or follow on Twitter and LinkedIn.</p><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin:0pt;"><font style="font-weight:bold;line-height:1.28;margin-bottom:8pt;visibility:hidden;">&#8203;</font></p><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin:0pt;"><b style="font-weight:bold;">About Silver Lake</b></p><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin:0pt;">Silver Lake is a global technology investment firm, with more than $95 billion in combined assets under management and committed capital and a team of professionals based in North America, Europe and Asia. Silver Lake&#8217;s portfolio companies collectively generate more than $282 billion of revenue annually and employ approximately 713,000 people globally.</p><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin:0pt;"><font style="font-weight:bold;line-height:1.28;margin-bottom:8pt;visibility:hidden;">&#8203;</font></p><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin:0pt;"><b style="font-weight:bold;">Forward Looking Statements</b></p><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin:0pt;"><font style="font-weight:bold;line-height:1.28;margin-bottom:8pt;visibility:hidden;">&#8203;</font></p><p style="font-family:'Calibri','Helvetica','sans-serif';font-size:11pt;line-height:1.19;margin:0pt;">Any statements made in this press release that are not statements of historical fact, including statements about our beliefs and expectations, are forward-looking statements and should be evaluated as such. Forward-looking statements include, among other things, statements about the anticipated benefits of the Pagero acquisition, the timing of completion of the Pagero acquisition and the issuance of the Convertible Preferred Stock and warrants, as well as the information concerning possible or assumed future results of operations, including descriptions of our business plan and strategies. &#x2022; Financed by combination of proceeds from its existing undrawn revolving credit facility and from issuance of a new series of Convertible Preferred
Stock in the amount of $500 million to Silver Lake
&#x2022; Convertible Preferred Stock is conditioned upon closing the acquisition and:
&#x2013; Carries a payment-in-kind dividend of 11.75%;
&#x2013; Convertible into Vertex common stock at an initial conversion price equal to a 20% premium over Vertex&#x2019;s trailing 10-day volume-weighted
average price as of December 19, 2023, subject to a minimum conversion price of $32.50 and a maximum of $37.50;
&#x2013; Subject to redemption and required repurchase on the terms and subject to the conditions set forth in the definitive agreements;
&#x2022; Silver Lake will be issued warrants to purchase up to 2.5 million additional shares of Vertex common stock at the conversion price
&#x2022; Joe Osnoss, a Managing Partner of Silver Lake, will join the Vertex Board of Directors upon transaction close
&#x2022; Annualized recurring revenue (ARR) is $71 million, representing approximately 38% year-over-year growth
&#x2022; SaaS business model with ~100% recurring revenue and 3-year ARR CAGR ~33%; average NRR ~120%
&#x2022; Pro forma acceleration of Vertex revenue growth by ~200 bps, and will be accretive to Vertex&#x2019;s margins in the second full year after closing (2026),
with additional opportunity to increase revenue synergies and cost benefits in the medium to long-term
&#x2022; Acceptance period of the offer is expected to commence on or around December 15, 2023 and expire on or around January 23, 2024
&#x2022; Offer is subject to certain regulatory approvals, the receipt of valid tenders of more than 90% of Pagero&#x2019;s shares and customary closing conditions
&#x2022; Assuming that the offer is declared unconditional after the acceptance period, settlement is expected to begin on or around February 1, 2024

Expansion into e-invoicing furthers Vertex&#x2019;s ability to provide an end-to-end
global compliance solution
6
&#x2022; In the EU alone, estimates on uncollected
VAT are ~&#x20AC;500bn
&#x2022; As accurate tax collection has become
much more difficult due to increased
regulation complexity, authorities around
the world are mandating
e-invoicing adoption
&#x2013; &gt; 50 countries rely on or have
announced intent to pass legislation
&#x2022; CTC and e-invoicing serve as a bridge
between AR compliance and AP
automation and provide taxing authorities
with more transactional data between
seller and buyers
&#x2022; Allows Vertex to capitalize on opportunity and
enter rapidly growing new global market with
established leader
&#x2022; Acquisition extends the breadth of Vertex
end-to-end solution
&#x2022; Enhances data analytics opportunities with
additional transaction level data across B2B,
B2G and G2B networks
&#x2022; Expands and deepens Vertex partner
ecosystem
&#x2022; Positions Vertex to expand in the &#x201C;Office of
the CFO&#x201D;, especially outside of the US
&#x2022; E-Invoicing is the digital exchange of structured
documents between buyers and suppliers
&#x2022; The digital infrastructure helps streamline the
invoicing process, reducing costs
&#x2022; Continuous Transaction Controls (CTC) are
mandated real-time and near real-time
reporting requirements whereby suppliers send
invoices to both tax authorities and buyers
directly
&#x2022; Required transaction data varies by jurisdiction
and changes over time
&#x2022; This also adds pressure on companies to
calculate tax correctly for each transaction,
as errors can delay the delivery of products
or services
Vertex Opportunity

// Edgar(tm) Renderer was created by staff of the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission.  Data and content created by government employees within the scope of their employment are not subject to domestic copyright protection. 17 U.S.C. 105.
var Show={};Show.LastAR=null,Show.showAR=function(a,r,w){if(Show.LastAR)Show.hideAR();var e=a;while(e&&e.nodeName!='TABLE')e=e.nextSibling;if(!e||e.nodeName!='TABLE'){var ref=((window)?w.document:document).getElementById(r);if(ref){e=ref.cloneNode(!0);
e.removeAttribute('id');a.parentNode.appendChild(e)}}
if(e)e.style.display='block';Show.LastAR=e};Show.hideAR=function(){Show.LastAR.style.display='none'};Show.toggleNext=function(a){var e=a;while(e.nodeName!='DIV')e=e.nextSibling;if(!e.style){}else if(!e.style.display){}else{var d,p_;if(e.style.display=='none'){d='block';p='-'}else{d='none';p='+'}
e.style.display=d;if(a.textContent){a.textContent=p+a.textContent.substring(1)}else{a.innerText=p+a.innerText.substring(1)}}}

/* Updated 2009-11-04 */
/* v2.2.0.24 */

/* DefRef Styles */
..report table.authRefData{
	background-color: #def;
	border: 2px solid #2F4497;
	font-size: 1em;
	position: absolute;
}

	display: block;
	font-weight: bold;
}

	margin-top: 0px;
}

	background-color: #2F4497;
	padding: 1px 3px 0px 0px;
	text-align: right;
}

	background-color: #2F4497;
}

	height: 150px;
	overflow: auto;
	width: 400px;
}

	font-size: 1em;
}

/* Report Styles */
..pl a, .pl a:visited {
	color: black;
	text-decoration: none;
}

	background-color: white;

	margin-bottom: 2em;
}

	border: 1px solid #acf;
}

	white-space: nowrap;
